This server requires certain dependencies.
Here's a list of the main dependencies you'll need to install, if not already installed:

Node.js
  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install nodejs
    To query node for its version number"
    node -v

npm
  Node Package Manager, usually comes with Node.js, if not:
    sudo apt install npm

Then, you'll need to install the following npm packages, if not already installed:
  npm install socket.io
  npm install express
  npm install pino pino-http
  npm install queue
  npm install bcrypt

Here's a breakdown of what each package is used for:
  socket.io: Real-time bidirectional event-based communication
  express: Web application framework for Node.js
  queue: Library for managing a queue of tasks
  pino: Library for logging
  pino-http: Pino as middleware for logging when used with Express

Lastly, create a package.json file if you haven't already:
  npm init -y

This will help manage project dependencies and scripts.
